<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-12-0376 </DOCNO><TEXT>The structure of (NbO){sub 2}P{sub 4}O{sub 13} is made up of zigzag anions[P{sub 4}O{sub 13}]{sup 6-} interleaved with niobyl cations NbO{sup 3+}forming a common framework. Despite the different symmetry of the structures,the general motif of the structure of (NbO){sub 2}P{sub 4}O{sub 13} isanalogous to that found in (MoO){sub 2}P{sub 4}O{sub 13}; the anions[P{sub 4}O{sub 13}]{sup 6-} in these two structures and in (NH{sub 4}){sub2}SiP{sub 4}O{sub 13} have similar configuration.</TEXT></DOC>